U.K. Tourist, Other Visits Rose 8% in Three Months Through May

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   R y a n
-- 
2011-07-14T09:42:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/u-k-tourist-other-visits-rose-8-in-three-months-through-may.html
Visits to the U.K. by tourists and
other visitors increased 8 percent to 7.8 million in the three
months through May from the previous three months, the  Office
for National Statistics  said today.  Earnings from overseas residents rose a seasonally adjusted
7 percent to 4.3 billion pounds ($6.9 billion),  the statistics
office  said in an e-mailed report. Visits were up 10 percent
from a year earlier.  Visits abroad by U.K. residents rose 11 percent from the
three months through February to 14.5 million, while their
expenditure outside Britain increased 7 percent to 7.8 billion
pounds. From a year earlier, travel abroad in the three months
through May was up 7 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Ryan in London at 
